<h2>Itching or burning and Worms in stool</h2>
<p>WebMD Symptom Checker helps you find the most common medical conditions indicated by the symptoms itching or burning and worms in stool including Pinworms, Ascaris worms, and Lice.</p>
<p>There  are 4 conditions  associated with itching or burning and worms in stool. The links below will provide you with more detailed information on these medical conditions from the WebMD Symptom Checker and help provide a better understanding of causes and treatment of these related conditions.</p>
</div>
<div class="related_conditions">
<ul class="results_list">
<li class="bg"><a href="http://symptoms.webmd.com/coresc/landing?condition=091e9c5e808e7bb4&amp;bpid[0]=35&amp;sid[0]=129&amp;bpid[1]=37&amp;sid[1]=451" onclick="return sl(this, '', 'sc-symindex-cmb_1');">Pinworms</a><p>Pinworms are small worms that infect the intestines and cause intense itching around the anus.</p>
</li>
<li><a href="http://symptoms.webmd.com/coresc/landing?condition=091e9c5e808e8203&amp;bpid[0]=35&amp;sid[0]=129&amp;bpid[1]=37&amp;sid[1]=451" onclick="return sl(this, '', 'sc-symindex-cmb_1');">Ascaris worms</a><p>Ascarisis is an infection by a roundworm, and can cause visible worms in the stool and respiratory symptoms.</p>
</li>
<li class="bg"><a href="http://symptoms.webmd.com/coresc/landing?condition=091e9c5e808e7c16&amp;bpid[0]=35&amp;sid[0]=129&amp;bpid[1]=37&amp;sid[1]=451" onclick="return sl(this, '', 'sc-symindex-cmb_1');">Lice</a><p>Head lice are tiny visible insects that infest the hair and scalp causing itchiness and bumps in that area.</p>
</li>
<li><a href="http://symptoms.webmd.com/coresc/landing?condition=091e9c5e808e8109&amp;bpid[0]=35&amp;sid[0]=129&amp;bpid[1]=37&amp;sid[1]=451" onclick="return sl(this, '', 'sc-symindex-cmb_1');">Crabs</a><p>Crabs, or pubic lice, are tiny, six-legged insects that infest pubic skin and hair and cause intense itching.</p>
</li>
</ul>
